The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, December 04, 2003  Red Chief impresses 
 BY OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT				 										Calcutta: Red Chief, Ever Lasting Love, Andropov and Shimmering River were impressive from among the following horses seen exercising on Wednesday:				 										Outer Sand track				 										1,800m: Accuser (C. Alford) in 2-23s; (600m) 50s; (400m) 32. Was unextended.				 										1,400m: Alashaan (C. Alford) and Amelina (Christopher) in 1-51s; (600m) 48s; (400m) 32s. The former moved well and finished 6 ls ahead.They are two-year-olds.				 										1,000m: Ever Lasting Love (R. Marshall) in 1-14s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 28s. Maintains fitness. May strike again. Deequa (R. Marshall) and Princess Xana (Rabani) in 1-16s; (600m) 45s; (400m) 31s. The former, who is in a forward condition, was easily 6 ls better. They are two-year-olds. Andropov (C. Alford) and Alsheim (Christopher) in 1-11s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 29s. Former, was 6 ls better. Note former.				 										800m: Among Men (Som ) and No Regrets (Rb) in 59s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 30s. Former was easily 5 ls better. Shadow Dancing (Surender) and Juneau (Rb) in 1-1s; (600m) 47s; (400m) 33s. They were easy while they worked level. Advancer (Christopher) and Aretino (C. Alford) in 56s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 29s. The former was 4 ls better but the latter was very easy. Red Chief (Merchant) and Another Time (Amil) in 54s; (600m) 40s; (400m) 28s. They former was hard held yet he finished 7 ls ahead. Amber Song (Merchant) and Smart Ruler (A. P. Singh) in 59s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 29s. They were handy while they worked level. King Nicholas (Amil) and Destiny Dance (R. Ahmed) in 58s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 30s. They moved well while working level. Calorific (C. Alford) and Reminiscent (Christopher) in 58s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 30s. They were level and were easy. They are two-year-olds. Shimmering River (Merchant) and Make A Wish (A. P. Singh) in 59s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 29s. The former was impressive while finishing 3 ls better. They are two-year-olds. Magic Feathers (R. Ahmed) and Bold Raider (Merchant) in 57s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 30s. Former was 2 ls better. Make a note of both. They are two-year-olds. Seeker (R. Marshall) in 56s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 28s. Coming on well. Keep an eye. Almelo (Christopher ) and Athinai (C. Alford) in 57s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 30s. Former 6 ls better and moved fluently. Bright And Clear (Gajender) and Flying Dash (Merchant) in 56s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 28s. They moved well while finishing level. Amicable (Rb) and Romantic Notes (Surender) in 1-1s; (600m) 46s; (400m) 32s. Former was far superior and also moved well.				 										On Tuesday, outer sand track				 										1,400m: Magic Mantra (Christopher) in 1-43s; (600m) 45s; (400m) 29s. Fit and forward. Hamilton (Christopher) (from 1,800m to 400m) in 1-45s; (first 800m) 56s. Was eased up in the last part.				 										1,000m: Psychic Flame (C. Alford) and Calamint (Christopher) in 1-11s; (600m) 41s; (400m) 29s. Former was distance better. Both moved easy.				 										800m: Aiberni (C. Alford) and Small Fry (Christopher) in 57s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 30s. The former who was 6 ls better, moved attractively. Compassionate (C. Alford) in 58s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 28s. Looking fit and forward. Anatolia (Christopher) and Modesto (C. Alford) in 58s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 30s. The former was impressive while finishing was 6 ls better, Azinger (R. Marshall) in 59s; (600m) 45s; (400m) 29s. Was unextended. Followme (R. Marshall) in 57s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 30s. Looking fit. Gypsy King (R. Marshall) in 58s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 28s. Maintaining fitness.				 										On Monday, outer sand track				 										1,400m: Acceptor (Islam) in 1-47s; (first 800m) 55s.Was eased up in the last part. 1,000m: Aretino (C. Alford) and Adderly (Christopher) in 1-22s; (600m) 49s; (400m) 32s. They were very easy while they finished level. 800m: Aperitivo (C. Alford) in 58s; (600m) 43s; (400m) 29s. Unextended. Note. Psychic Flame (C. Alford) in 57s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 28s. Maintaining her fitness. Triumphant (Kujur) in 1-0s; (600m) 45s; (400m) 30s. Easy. 				 										Sand track				 										800m: Sagittarian (A. Hassan) in 57s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 27s. Easy.
